definition: Pierre Robin malformation is a sequence of developmental malformations characterized by micrognathia (mandibular hypoplasia), glossoptosis and cleft palate.

A delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child, including motor skills, speech and language, cognitive skills, and social and emotional skills. This term should only be used to describe children younger than five years of age.

The onset of secondary sexual characteristics before a normal age. Although it is difficult to define normal age ranges because of the marked variation with which puberty begins in normal children, precocious puberty can be defined as the onset of puberty before the age of 8 years in girls or 9 years in boys.

Cerebellar ataxia refers to ataxia due to dysfunction of the cerebellum. This causes a variety of elementary neurological deficits including asynergy (lack of coordination between muscles, limbs and joints), dysmetria (lack of ability to judge distances that can lead to under- oder overshoot in grasping movements), and dysdiadochokinesia (inability to perform rapid movements requiring antagonizing muscle groups to be switched on and off repeatedly).
The presence of chronic increased pressure in the systemic arterial system.
Abnormal (retrograde) movement of urine from the bladder into ureters or kidneys related to inadequacy of the valvular mechanism at the ureterovesicular junction or other causes.
A degree of language development that is significantly below the norm for a child of a specified age.
Any structural abnormality of a lingual artery.

Impairment of certain skills such as reading or writing, coordination, self-control, or attention that interfere with the ability to learn. The impairment is not related to a global deficiency of intelligence.
An increased concentration of cholesterol in the blood.
A type of diabetes mellitus initially characterized by insulin resistance and hyperinsulinemia and subsequently by glucose interolerance and hyperglycemia.

A chronic condition in which the pancreas produces little or no insulin. Type I diabetes mellitus is manifested by the sudden onset of severe hyperglycemia with rapid progression to diabetic ketoacidosis unless treated with insulin.
Underdevelopment of the external ear.
An early onset of puberty, in this case early does not refer to precocious.
One or both of the leaflets (cusps) of the mitral valve bulges back into the left atrium upon contraction of the left ventricle.
Any structural anomaly of the mouth, which is also known as the oral cavity.
An abnormally increased chloride concentration in the blood.

Recurrent attacks of acute inflammatory arthritis of a joint or set of joints caused by elevated levels of uric acid in the blood which crystallize and are deposited in joints, tendons, and surrounding tissues.
Asthma is characterized by increased responsiveness of the tracheobronchial tree to multiple stimuli, leading to narrowing of the air passages with resultant dyspnea, cough, and wheezing.
An abnormality of the mouth.
Immunological states where the immune system produces harmful responses upon reexposure to sensitising antigens.
An abnormality of chloride homeostasis or concentration in the body.
An abnormality of a blood vessel of the head, including branches of the arterial and venous systems of the head.
synonyms: Abnormality of blood vessel of head

definition: Any structural anomaly of the tongue.
A deviation from normal of the neurological development of a child, which may include any or all of the aspects of the development of personal, social, gross or fine motor, and cognitive abilities.
A functional abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder.
An abnormality of the systemic arterial tree, which consists of the aorta and other systemic arteries.
synonyms: Abnormality of the systemic arterial tree

definition: Abnormal increase in blood pressure. An individual measurement of increased blood pressure does not necessarily imply hypertension. In practical terms, multiple measurements are recommended to diagnose the presence of hypertension.
A group of abnormalities characterized by hyperglycemia and glucose intolerance.
An anomaly of the control or production of movement in the central nervous system.
Dysfunction of the urinary bladder.
Any structural anomaly of the mitral valve.
Inflammation of a joint.
The presence of aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of all or part of the external ear.
Any deviation from the normal concentration of cholesterol in the blood circulation.
An abnormality of the pinna, which is also referred to as the auricle or external ear.
The presence of aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the ear.
Abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of a monoatomic ion.
An abnormality of the vasculature.
An abnormality of the head.
An abnormal structure or form of the joints, i.e., one or more of the articulations where two bones join.
Any abnormality of the tongue.
A functional anomaly of the nervous system.

Glucose intolerance (GI) can be defined as dysglycemia that comprises both prediabetes and diabetes. It includes the conditions of impaired fasting glucose (IFG) and impaired glucose tolerance (IGT) and diabetes mellitus (DM).
An abnormality of an atrioventricular valve.
A chronic deviation from normal pressure in the systemic arterial system.
An abnormality of the face.
An abnormality of the external ear.
An abnormality of the urinary bladder.
An abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder.
A functional abnormality of the immune system.
An abnormality in the of lipid metabolism.
An abnormality of the lower urinary tract.
phenotype_name: Abnormality of the lower urinary tract

definition: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.
Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.
Any structural anomaly of the ear.
An abnormal level of an analyte measured in the blood.
An abnormality of the upper urinary tract.
phenotype_name: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract
synonyms: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract

definition: Abnormality of the oral cavity, i.e., the opening or hollow part of the mouth.
Any structural abnormality of a cardiac valve.
Any structural anomaly of the heart and great vessels.
Abnormality of glucose homeostasis.
An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.
An abnormality of the urinary system.
Any structural anomaly of the heart.
